+## Lab ownership (edit tokens)
+
+There's no account system yet, so labs are protected by a per-lab secret (`editToken`) instead. It's generated when a lab is created, returned once in the creation response, and saved client-side (`src/lib/labEditTokens.ts`, currently `localStorage`). Updating or deleting a lab requires sending that token back in an `X-Edit-Token` header; without it, those routes return 403. This isn't real multi-user auth — anyone with the token (e.g. someone who clears their browser storage, or switches devices) loses the ability to edit that lab — it just stops a stranger who only has the public student share link from tampering with or deleting a lab. The real fix is wiring up BetterAuth below.
+
 ## Adding BetterAuth
 
